  "repo_truth": "Review the exact remediated 55-path worktree subject against baseline fd6242fbab911eebb09a4d541a6e5e1e32dc5468. Review 5 found that two success-path refusal-precedence tests omitted the now-required selected Project Context, causing strict-read refusal before BudgetRefused or UnsupportedRequest. The parent now Unix-gates those success-path tests, writes the valid canonical Project Context runtime fixture in each, and cfg-gates their Unix-only imports/helper. Windows passes all 6 applicable refusal-mapping tests with no test-owned warning; Linux passes all 9 and reaches both intended precedence outcomes. Existing dedicated non-Unix strict selected-read coverage remains in flow/compiler/engine tests. Review-4 remediations and prior proof remain unchanged. Preserve the shipped HCM-1.4 conditional INDETERMINATE contract.",
  "allowed_scope": [
    "Remain read-only and replay all 55 manifest hashes plus the aggregate before reviewing.",
    "Re-review every production and test byte, with priority on the review-5 refusal-precedence remediation and all prior Required findings.",
    "Run bounded read-only Rust, filesystem, API-surface, security, portability, and smoke-logic checks as needed.",
    "Return findings first with exact file/line evidence and the smallest in-scope remediation."
  ],
  "non_goals": [
